<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Letter</div>
<div class="nbunit" id="22Jul1932"><font color="red">22 July 1932</font> <i>Letters III</i> (to Harriet Weaver): My father sent me a message by a friend in the curious roundabout delicate and allusive way he had in spite of all his elaborate curses (he is quoted on the jacket of an amusing book <i>Lars Porsena</i> or <i>The Future of Swearing</i>) that if I thought fit he would like a tombstone to be placed on his grave bearing the names of himself and my mother </div>
